summary.summary: CVD-Dataset is a Docker container providing access to the repository storing the Cardio- Vascular Disease dataset . This project has received funding from the European Union 's Horizon 2020 research and innovation program under grant agreement 825619 AI4EU . The project is based on the data that is being used to build a repository for the Cardi-Vascular Disease Dataset dataset . The dataset is stored in the Docker container . The CVD Datasets are stored in a container that is used to store the data from the repository of the CVD dataset . Data is stored on Docker containers in the repository . The data is used for the repository to create a repository that contains the dataset for the dataset. The data includes a Docker Docker container. The dataset includes a container containing a container for the data. It contains a container with a container. It includes a docker container containing an image of the data to create the data for a container and a container to make it easier to use. The AI4Datasets. dataset. It has been used to create an environment for the project’s CVD. Datasettes. It is available in a Docker Container for the purposes of AI4. Datatations. The Data Datatats.

GTA Dataset GTA Dataset Grand Traffic Auto Dataset Dataset http: / / aimh.isti.cnr.it / grand_traffic_auto / Developed by National Research Council License GNU General Public License ( GPL ) v3 Main Characteristic The GTA – Grand Traffic Auto dataset is a vast collection of about 15 , 000 _ synthetic _ images of urban traffic scenes collected using the highly photo- realistic graphical engine of the _ GTA V – Grand Theft Auto V _ video game .
About half of them concern urban city areas , while the remaining involve sub- urban areas and highways .

Research areas Physical AI Technical Categories Computer vision Business Categories Transportation Keywords Synthetic Datasets Visual counting Last updated 22.06.2021 - 13:25 Detailed Description Additional information : To generate this dataset , we designed a framework that automatically and precisely annotates the vehicles present in the scene with per-pixel annotations .
To the best of our knowledge , this is the first instance segmentation synthetic dataset of city traffic scenarios .
Trustworthy AI We are not impacted by Trustworthy AI requirements .
GDPR Requirements This dataset is GDPR compliant .
It was manually collected by its authors .
